Es lebten einmal die alten Mnner Schmetterling und Krcke.
Once there lived the old men Butterfly and Crutch.
Sie leben weit voneinander entfernt, sie kennen einander.
They live far from each other, they know each other.
Birgehe ol diek dielek, birgehe ba diek dielek.
Der eine hat ein Haus in diese Richtung, der andere hat ein Haus in jene Richtung.
One of them has a house in this direction, the other one has a house in that direction.
Sie leben und treffen sich zu zweit, sie unterhalten sich.
Living so they meet and chat with each other.
"Ka", (dir) deheller Lrtn gtta Tanaktak ogonnor, "ka bihigi (bi-) bir dl bhar asptn birge kolbommut ahak."
"Hey", besprechen die alten Mnner Schmetterling und Krcke, "lass uns unsere Nahrung, die fr ein Jahr reicht, zusammenlegen und essen."
"Well", the old men Butterfly and Crutch discuss, "let us put together our food, which is enough for one year, and let us eat it."
"Badakptna badaga (bi-) uhunnuk oloruokput, badaga, dlbtn bharbtgar dagn.
"Wenn wir wollen, leben wir wohl lange, wenn wir nur durch das Jahr kommen.
"If we want, we will live long, if we only come through the year.
An oogo bihigi, Lr, eniene (()) askn ahak."
Jetzt dann, Schmetterling, lass uns dein Essen essen."
Then now, Butterfly, let us eat your food."
"E, Tanaktak ogonnor, gini ol, giniene dietiger barammt ahak."
"Ja, alter Mann Krcke, lass uns in sein Haus gehen und essen."
"Yes, old man Crutch, let us go into his house and eat."
They are eating in Butterfly's house.
Eine Hlfte, bis die alle ist.
One half, until it runs out.

Well, having eaten their food ran out, Butterfly's one.
"Nun, gehen wir zum alten Mann Krcke."
"Well, let us go to the old man Crutch."
Sie gehen und fangen an, seine Nahrung zu essen.
They go and start eating his food.
O, Tanaktak ogonnorgo bardlar ((PAUSE)) de ahllar.

Oh, they went to the old man Crutch and they eat.

"Well", one friend [says], "my food is about to run out", he says, "go home.

Fr dich selbst jagend, ich mchte nicht alle meine Nahrung aufessen."
Hunting for yourself, I don't want to eat up all my food."

He cooks it for himself and sits.
Ka, onton krbte, tugu ere bultammt emie Lr.
Nun, dann sah er, dass er sich wieder etwas gejagt hatte, Schmetterling.
Well, then he saw, he again had hunt something, Butterfly.
Onton majdn, Tanaktak ogonnor da aha barammt ete hopsiem.
Dann von jenem, vom alten Mann Krcke war sein Essen ganz zu Ende gegangen.
Then the food of that one, of the old man Crutch has run out completely.
Nun er sitzt, er bert sich nicht mit ihm.
Well, he sits, he doesn't take counsel with him.
"De kelbetin gini, bejem da bultanan oloron bir tuokkan eme", dir.
"Nun, soll er nicht kommen, ich lebe und jage fr mich selbst, irgendwas", denkt er.
"Well, he shall not come, I am hunting and living for myself, something", he thinks.
Wie er so lebte, kam der alte Mann Krcke.
As he was living so, the old man Crutch came.
Er sah, wie er ging, sein Freund.
He saw how he was going, his friend.
"B, Tanaktak ogonnor iher ebit", Lr dir, (()) dietin katanan, haban kespit.

"Oh, the old man Crutch is going apparently", Butterfly thinks () and locked his house.

He came and sang again to Butterfly:

He went and as we was just arriving, he arrives beneath his house, he saw that a female reindeer with a calf is going around his house.
Kaja kelitten kelbite dr bilbet taban gini (()) taba hldar araj, kelbit.
Woher auch immer es kam, er kennt das Rentier nicht () das Rentier geht nur, es kam.

r gini lk jaggar, (t-) tilliek jaggar tuguttak thta bejetiger kelen hal hldbttar ginini.

Well, he skinned that out, cooked the raw [meat], cooked and ate it.
Nun seine Augen wurden da heller.
Well, his eyes got lighter then.
"O, de an bagas abrannm, Lrge barbappn, kanabappn, astannm buo", dir.
"Oh, jetzt bin ich gerettet, ich gehe nicht zu Schmetterling und so, ich habe doch Essen bekommen", denkt er.
"Oh, no I am saved, I don't go to Butterfly, I got food though", he thinks.
Der Mensch, der Essen bekommen hat, kocht es sich und isst.
The human, who has gotten food, cooks and eats it.
Nun, wie viele Tage lebte er so.
Well, how many days he lived like that.

He has a reindeer, he has caught the reindeer, the female reindeer.

"De min an itigirdik gnam, bebe kellin agaj", diebit, "minieke as".

"Well, I'll make it the same way, shall he come", he thought, "I have food here."
Lr tuoktan ar iher buopsa korgujan.

He is hardly able to walk.

at my day there stood, if you are an inanimate human, old man Crutch, old man Crutch", he sang for himself.

"Go home", he said, "don't come again, not long ago you tortured me, too."

What shall that one do, he went.

Again he went and the next morning, after several days have passed, he comes again.

Well, he was apparently close to die, his friend, Butterfly reached his limits:

When he chases him, he doesn't run away, if he goes in, he doesn't come.

Feeling sorry he can't do nothing, chasing him () he goes and won't arrive at home.
() wenn es so ist: "Komm rein", sagte er, "iss, lass uns dann gut unterhalten."

They gave advise to each other, they were sly, they live in richness and satiety, that's the end.
